race.comment: PARISIENNE PIPER (3) has had a few chances but looks to be on the doorstep of a maiden victory placing at her past couple around this circuit. Gets some weight relief with the 2kg claim and should be right there when the whips are cracking. ZEDIQUETTE (4) may have suffered from the dreaded second-up syndrome last time out but go on the solid runner-up finish here when resuming. Drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley and is capable of bouncing back to form against this lot. OLD FAITHFUL (1) has been in the betting in both starts to date and where there's smoke there's fire. Keep safe. FULL STRENGTH (2) will be rock-hard fit for this and may earn some minor money. HAPPY COFFEE (6) next in line.
